Suricata Installation & Configuration (Kali Linux)

A beginner-friendly Suricata Intrusion Detection System (IDS) setup for home lab practice and demonstration.

Environment:
Virtualization: Hyper-V
OS: Kali GNU/Linux 2025.2
Suricata Version: [to be filled after install]

Step 1: Update Kali packages
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

Step 2: Install Suricata
sudo apt install suricata -y

Step 3: Check version
suricata --build-info | grep version

Step 4: Check if itâ€™s running
sudo systemctl status suricata

Basic Configuration
Set HOME_NET in Suricata YAML config
sudo nano /etc/suricata/suricata.yaml

Find the section:
vars:
  address-groups:
    HOME_NET: "[192.168.0.0/16]"
Your HOME_NET is your VM's internal IP address range

 Edit the Config File
sudo nano /etc/suricata/suricata.yaml
